    <text>
        <body>
      
		<pb n="1"/>
			<p><add><hi rend="underline">Hebrew</hi></add></p>
          <p rend="indent(2)"><placeName>Pittsburgh</placeName>&#8212;<date>1853</date></p>
          <p rend="indent(3)">&#40;evidently during <date>Succoth</date>&#41;</p>
			<p>To my dear friend&#44; rabbi&#44; sage&#44; honored&#44;<lb/> famous etc. etc.</p>
			<p>My friend&#44;</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">In going to <placeName>Cleveland</placeName> I stopped here<lb/> until after <date>Yom Kippur</date>&#44; and found here a<lb/> fine and worthy congregation&#44; with men of<lb/> parts and learning&#44; good and true. I also<lb/> found here one of the sons of <persName>Mr. Yaroslavsky</persName><lb/> with whom I used to be acquainted in <placeName>Charleston</placeName><lb/> In the evening we discussed their congregational<lb/> matters&#44; and the conversation turned upon me.<lb/> In sum&#44; they consented that I stay with<lb/> them. I <del>have found</del> find myself&#44; therefore&#44;<lb/> obliged to let you know at once. To<lb/> myself I apply the Biblical verse&#44; &#8220;God<lb/> will hear when I call upon Him&#44;&#8221; for God<lb/> has helped me. The people of <placeName>Montgomery</placeName><lb/> had said that they would do everything<lb/> in their power to prevent me from obtain&#45;<lb/>ing a position anywhere in <placeName>America</placeName>&#44;<lb/> and I apply to myself &#8220;Thus do I know</p>
		<pb n="2"/>
			<p>that you delight in me&#44; that mine enemy<lb/> will not shout over me&#8221;&#42; I am sure<lb/> that you will stand by my just cause and<lb/> will support me and give me aid&#44; and renew<lb/> my station as of old. This I must ask you<lb/> <del>that if</del> in case any thing new takes place with<lb/> regard to the well&#45;known affair <add>&#63;</add><lb/> Also please&#44; for God&#39;s sake&#44; send me the<lb/> address of <persName>Mr. Yaroslavsky</persName>&#44; and I shall return<lb/> it.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">I am certain&#44; that&#44; with God&#39;s help&#44; I<lb/> shall find rest here&#44; and will be able to<lb/> study English. By the hand of a traveler<lb/> in the near future I shall send what I owe<lb/> for the Occident which you will please send<lb/> to the above address. You&#44; my friend are<lb/> &#63; an unusual man and I am unable to<lb/> write a letter fit for a man like you. Therefore<lb/> I ask your pardon for this letter. I am<lb/> sure you will not give credence to slanderers&#44;<lb/> and will not be <del>from</del> among the purveyors of<lb/> slander.</p>
			<p>&#42;Ps. 41&#58;12</p>
		<pb n="3"/>
			<p>May God extend your years in joy. That is<lb/> my wish and that of all friends.</p>
			<p rend="&#8220;these rhyme&#8221; written in left margin next to following lines">Looking for your reply<lb/>Trusting in your aid&#44;<lb/>and in the aid of Him Who guards this congregation<lb/>the Congregation of <placeName>Jeshurun</placeName> His chosen one<lb/>and who calls it His only one&#44;<lb/>just as He is one and only.<lb/>And the righteous shall live by his faith.</p>
          <p rend="indent(2)"><persName role="author">Menachem Elya Marcussohn</persName></p>
          
        </body>
